Comment:
Dear Dr. Niemeier;
Farmworker Justice, Health Outreach Partners, Migrant Clinicians Network, and the National Center for Farmworker Health submit these written comments in response to NIOSH’s Draft Hazard Review: Wildland Fire Smoke Exposure Among Farmworkers and other Outdoor Workers. Our organizations, as members of the Farmworker Health Network, provide training and technical assistance to health centers that serve migratory and seasonal farmworkers and their families.
Farmworkers are on the frontline of climate change and wildfire smoke exposure has become an increasing health threat. We appreciate NIOSH’s extensive work on the development of the Hazard Review. We support the proposed exposure assessment and control strategies to ensure the protection of farmworkers from wildfire smoke. As NIOSH continues its work, we want to emphasize the following:
